    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Health&#44; Prosperity and Happiness.<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>New Year 5639.<lb/>
                Cincinnati 1878.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>When this reaches<lb/> you with the blessing of God a<lb/> New Year will have dawned<lb/> upon us&#44; God grant it may be<lb/> a year of health and prosperity<lb/> to us all&#44; that all our antic<lb/>ipations may be realized.<lb/></p>
            <p>We part with its cares and<lb/> anxieties&#44; its trials and tribulations<lb/> are now among the past.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>On the advent of the New Year<lb/> may it please the Almighty to re&#45;<lb/>move the direful scourge that now<lb/> hovers over the towns of the north.<lb/>  Heal those who &#91;&#63;&#93; &#91;&#63;&#93; in<lb/> anguish on their sick&#45;beds&#44; send<lb/> consolation to the afflicted and re&#45;<lb/>lief to the widow and orphans&#44;<lb/> may this be the will of God.<lb/></p>
            <p>I trust the coming festivals<lb/> may be a season of enjoyment<lb/> to us all with our dear families<lb/> We expect crowded Temples and<lb/> Synagogues during the Holy days<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>as there are many strangers<lb/> here from the south.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr Wise will lecture on the 2d<lb/> day of R. H. at a conservative<lb/> synagogue&#44; he told me to day<lb/> that a new move will be innau<lb/>gurated to observe the sabbath here<lb/> with the largest houses as the Par&#45;<lb/>nass of his Temple who is in one<lb/> of the largest establishments here<lb/> says he will not hold the office if<lb/> the male attendance is not incli&#45;<lb/>ned to observe the sabbath and attend<lb/> the service.  God grant it may be so&#44;<lb/> and I think it will be carried out.<lb/>  One student &#91;&#63;&#93; is much pleased<lb/> with Cincinnati&#44; the school and<lb/> College&#44; also his home.  The students<lb/> are compelled to have morning service<lb/> every day at their dormitory.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>Hoping this may meet you<lb/> and dear ones well&#44; and that<lb/> dear Nina is better from the ef&#45;<lb/>fects of the cold she contracted<lb/> and with love to all&#44; and from<lb/> our dear ones to you and yours<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain as ever<lb/>
                Truly &#38;c<lb/>
                Jacob Ezekiel</p>
        </body>
